review_id:
Best aland pancake on the island.

Cafe has a very central location and accessible for everyone. Prices are pretty average for the island.

Especially recommended during the summer months, but it can also be nice to sit by the large panorama window and watch people pass by during the winter months while enjoying a warm drink.

review_id:
Cafe smelled like freshly baked pannkaka when we arrived and we had a nice encounter with friendly staff.

I was planning to take the pannkaka however I didn't as they served fresh smorbulla (~butter bun) which is very traditional sweetbun and a rare find these days. It's bit tricky to make and takes longer to prepare. Also it's not such a modern product so that's why it's not found in many places.

I appreciate when I find it and was not disappointed! Semi-sweet and full of flavor.

I thank for this experience I was not waiting but what I fully enjoyed.
